<span id="freeTextContainer5719902662330180711">I am a writer, educator, businessperson and former Central Intelligence Agency senior operations officer. After receiving a master&apos;s degree at Stanford University, I wrote my first non-fiction book, &quot;The McCarthy Era: 1950-1954 - Was American Society Threatened?&quot; while teaching high school in Cupertino, California. Following two tours of duty in Vietnam as a U.S. Army military intelligence adviser</span>
  <span id="freeText5719902662330180711" style="display:none">I am a writer, educator, businessperson and former Central Intelligence Agency senior operations officer. After receiving a master's degree at Stanford University, I wrote my first non-fiction book, "The McCarthy Era: 1950-1954 - Was American Society Threatened?" while teaching high school in Cupertino, California. Following two tours of duty in Vietnam as a U.S. Army military intelligence adviser, I stayed on in Asia for two decades as a businessperson in Hong Kong, the Philippines and Japan. Returning to the U.S. and managing a laser and sensor manufacturing company in Los Angeles, I subsequently accepted a position as an operations officer in the Central Intelligence Agency. This enabled me to return to work overseas, primarily in the Middle East and the former Soviet Union. I am now self-employed and, in January of 2010, published a spy-thriller novel, "The Wave of the Future." My wife, Joan, and I currently live outside Washington, DC, along the Potomac River in Southern Maryland, where I am working on another spy-thriller. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5719902662330180711" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

